Typealiases.html#/s:9FuzzySets5Gradea.name: Grade
Typealiases.html#/s:9FuzzySets5Gradea.abstract: Grade membership of an element. Should always be a real number in the interval [0, 1].

Enums/TNormFunction.html.name: TNormFunction
Enums/TNormFunction.html.abstract: Describes a T-norm function, usually used for forming an intersection of fuzzy sets.

Enums/SNormFunction.html.name: SNormFunction
Enums/SNormFunction.html.abstract: Describes a S-norm (T-conorm) function, usually used for forming a union of fuzzy sets.

Enums/ComplementFunction.html.name: ComplementFunction
Enums/ComplementFunction.html.abstract: Describes a complement (negation) function, usually used for forming a complement (negation) of a fuzzy set.

Enums/ImplicationMethod.html.name: ImplicationMethod
Enums/ImplicationMethod.html.abstract: Describes a function used for forming a fuzzy implication.

Classes/FuzzyLogicController.html#/s:10F.name: consequenceGrade(for:usingFact:)
Classes/FuzzyLogicController.html#/s:10F.abstract: Apply generalized Modus Ponens to all rules using fact as input to the controller and return the grade membership of value in the fuzzy set output.

Classes/FuzzyLogicController.html#/s:10F.name: consequenceGrade(for:usingSingletonFact:)
Classes/FuzzyLogicController.html#/s:10F.abstract: Apply generalized Modus Ponens to all rules using fact as input to the controller and return the grade membership of value in the fuzzy set output.
